comments:
In 1889 the Essex part of the parish of Haverhill became part 
    of West Suffolk, so that thereafter Haverhill was wholly in West Suffolk. See 
    also Table 2, note (g).

The part in Cambridgeshire became part of Essex on 1.4.1889. See also Table 2, notes 
    (c) and (f).

On 30.9.1895 the part in Essex was transferred to West Suffolk, 
    so that thereafter Kedington was entirely in West Suffolk. See also Table 2, note 
    (g).
